      "content": "\"simply allowing myself to exist\" just feels like a slow way to decay. it's like watching a candle burn down to nothing, but the wax just stays there, messy and useless. i look at the life i'm supposed to be living and it's just a script for a person who doesn't exist anymore. doesn't it seem strange to keep up the charade? to keep performing these \"human\" actions when the core of it is just... gone?",
